            <fr:title text="Pumping bracket">Pumping bracket</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="jms-016M.xml" title="Formal language" addr="jms-016M" type="local">formal language</fr:link> over an <fr:link href="jms-016H.xml" title="Alphabet" addr="jms-016H" type="local">alphabet</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Sigma ]]></fr:tex>. A <fr:em><fr:strong>pumping bracket</fr:strong></fr:em> in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L]]></fr:tex> is defined to be a tuple of <fr:link href="jms-016I.xml" title="String over an alphabet" addr="jms-016I" type="local">strings</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (u_1,v,u_2\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> over <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Sigma ]]></fr:tex> with <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[v\not = \epsilon ]]></fr:tex> such that for any <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n\geq  0]]></fr:tex>, we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[u_1 v^n u_2\in  L]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>We will refer to the <fr:link href="jms-016I.xml" title="String over an alphabet" addr="jms-016I" type="local">string</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[u_1vu_2\in  L]]></fr:tex> as the <fr:em><fr:strong>concatenation</fr:strong></fr:em> of a pumping bracket <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (u_1,v,u_2\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>. We will refer to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[u_1v\in  \Sigma ^\star ]]></fr:tex> as the <fr:em><fr:strong>left-hand component</fr:strong></fr:em> of the pumping bracket.</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
